com.intellinum.mia.app.runtime

Class Session

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellinum.mia.app.runtime.Session

  • public class Session
extends java.lang.Object
    Session class when a client create a connection to server This class possess most of the information regarding the session Information like, source application, source page, source field, previous page, previous field and etc. Database connection can be retrieved from here too. Any object can be store in here.

      • loadTranslation

        public void loadTranslation(java.lang.String pageID)
        Load language translation. This function should only be called from the DynamicPage constructor. In the translationManager class, it store the pageID as the latest ID, so if it was called in the other place, it might mess up with that pageID. If there is a need to use a load translation, then it's better to create a new function instead of reusing this one. (Ideally we should store the pageID in the translationManager, but if we don't do that, then every UI component, would need to store pageID, so that during the translation they can pass the pageID. Logically this is a better way, but to much work to change all the component.)
        Parameters:
        pageID -
